What is Java?
Java is a popular programming language, created in 1995.

It is owned by Oracle, and devloped by james gosling, more than 3 billion devices run Java.

It is used for:

Mobile applications (specially Android apps)
Desktop applications
Web applications
Web servers and application servers
Games
Database connection

